adjectives.description: disinterested (comparative more disinterested, superlative most disinterested)

entries.meaning: Having no stake or interest in the outcome, and no conflicts of interest; free of bias, impartial. [from 17th c.]
examples: People are better off abjuring violence, if everyone else agrees to do so, and vesting authority in a disinterested third party.
How dis-interested are they in all Worldly matters, since they fling their Wealth and Riches into the Sea.
